03:55.058 --> 03:58.184
I don't remember how therapy ended.

03:58.811 --> 04:00.811
That's because you weren't here.

04:03.353 --> 04:04.696
I blacked out?

04:05.643 --> 04:07.978
Do you know what happens
to you when you black out?

04:11.416 --> 04:12.416
No.

04:14.643 --> 04:17.642
I think there might be other
people living with you.

04:19.644 --> 04:22.879
Have you ever heard of
dissociative identity disorder?

04:24.844 --> 04:25.756
No.

04:27.643 --> 04:29.602
When a child experiences trauma,

04:29.644 --> 04:32.601
they sometimes disappear
inside themselves

04:32.643 --> 04:34.936
in order to handle it.

04:34.978 --> 04:37.601
They create other
personas who can come out

04:37.643 --> 04:39.485
and deal with it better.

04:40.811 --> 04:43.874
I spoke to someone at
the end of our session.

04:45.643 --> 04:46.854
It wasn't you.

04:50.134 --> 04:51.839
Well, who... who was it?

04:52.643 --> 04:53.487
Your mother

04:54.145 --> 04:56.513
or a version of her you've created.

04:59.643 --> 05:00.601
What did she say?

05:00.643 --> 05:02.601
(INHALES DEEPLY)

05:02.643 --> 05:04.103
She wants to protect you.

05:04.145 --> 05:05.312
From what?

05:07.168 --> 05:09.030
I think me, at the moment.

05:10.449 --> 05:12.408
Do you have any awareness of her?

05:12.644 --> 05:15.601
<i>(EERIE MUSIC)</i>

05:19.978 --> 05:23.845
There have been a... a few
times that I've been confused,

05:24.643 --> 05:28.601
have thought I spoke to
my mother but hadn't.

05:28.643 --> 05:29.861
That's good.

05:30.643 --> 05:34.145
Can you remember any
details of those events?

05:37.643 --> 05:39.295
Not really.

05:40.643 --> 05:41.731
No.

05:43.224 --> 05:45.601
But, um, you said...

05:45.643 --> 05:49.103
Why... why does she want
to protect me from you?

05:49.497 --> 05:50.795
I don't know yet.

05:52.643 --> 05:53.602
Oh.

05:53.921 --> 05:55.601
We've been in here almost two weeks,

05:55.643 --> 05:58.596
and you've spoken very little
about your life growing up.

05:59.643 --> 06:03.601
I was, uh...

06:04.003 --> 06:05.421
normal.

06:09.643 --> 06:10.601
My parents fought a bit.

06:10.643 --> 06:14.478
Uh, my dad had a drinking problem.

06:14.520 --> 06:16.601
But every family has their problems.

06:16.643 --> 06:19.601
It was nothing, uh, extraordinary.

06:19.643 --> 06:20.601
It was ordinary.

06:20.643 --> 06:22.007
You know, they both tried.

06:23.425 --> 06:25.728
I don't really remember
that much about it.

06:26.643 --> 06:28.643
Really, you know, I-I...

06:29.508 --> 06:30.600
My dad was gone a lot.

06:30.642 --> 06:33.285
I just mostly remember
being with my mother,

06:34.280 --> 06:36.601
which was nice.

06:41.353 --> 06:43.601
My head... my head just
still hurts a lot.

06:43.643 --> 06:46.601
I get these bad headaches
when I black out.

06:47.174 --> 06:48.601
Can we not do this today?

06:48.643 --> 06:49.602
Okay, Norman.

06:50.419 --> 06:52.423
You need to rest and
take care of yourself.

06:53.243 --> 06:54.602
We can meet tomorrow.

06:55.263 --> 06:56.644
Thank you, Doctor.

07:01.643 --> 07:03.643
Oh, um...

07:06.643 --> 07:07.601
(DOOR CLICKS SHUT)

07:07.643 --> 07:09.508
What was this person like?

07:11.059 --> 07:13.169
This person in me who's my mother?

07:16.482 --> 07:18.440
Actually, she's charming.

07:25.513 --> 07:26.471
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

07:26.513 --> 07:28.471
(SOFT COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING)

07:28.513 --> 07:31.471
(DOOR CLICKS OPEN, BELL JINGLING)

07:39.099 --> 07:40.934
Thanks for coming to meet me.

07:40.977 --> 07:43.058
That's quite a cane you got there.

07:43.100 --> 07:44.393
Yeah, I made it.

07:44.435 --> 07:46.058
Carved it myself.

07:46.100 --> 07:47.563
What is that, birch?

07:48.100 --> 07:49.588
Honeysuckle vine.

07:51.267 --> 07:53.058
Love it. I love that you made it.

07:53.100 --> 07:56.058
It's amazing what we can do

07:56.100 --> 07:58.653
when we have to do it.

08:01.100 --> 08:04.547
So you had any thoughts
about our little talk?

08:05.100 --> 08:06.619
Well...

08:13.100 --> 08:14.775
I'm not sure what you're asking me,

08:16.100 --> 08:17.489
and that's why I wanted to meet you.

08:18.100 --> 08:19.059
Mm-hmm.

08:19.525 --> 08:22.673
I-I like that thing you do.

08:24.574 --> 08:27.916
You know, between the... your poses.

08:31.618 --> 08:34.100
Are you lonely, Norma Bates?

08:35.100 --> 08:38.058
Uh, no.

08:38.100 --> 08:41.393
I just suspected that
you might be lonely

08:41.434 --> 08:44.058
because you can't share
with the people you love

08:44.100 --> 08:47.560
the fact that you had
sex with your brother.

08:48.188 --> 08:49.644
Can I get you anything?

08:49.687 --> 08:51.710
I'll have a club sandwich.

08:51.753 --> 08:53.100
No mayo.

08:57.602 --> 08:58.869
For you, ma'am?

09:00.100 --> 09:02.377
I'm not eating, thank you.

09:03.419 --> 09:05.353
You're so polite.

09:06.100 --> 09:07.058
I love it, there's not a lot

09:07.100 --> 09:09.058
of polite people left in this world,

09:09.100 --> 09:11.395
but you're, like, genuinely sweet.

09:13.087 --> 09:15.029
So what the hell happened,

09:15.162 --> 09:16.768
you fiddling bits with your brother?

09:16.810 --> 09:19.813
- Would you stop saying that?
- What? It happened.

09:19.913 --> 09:23.058
- But...
- Not saying it is not gonna undo it.

09:23.100 --> 09:25.058
So just come on.

09:25.100 --> 09:26.058
I dare you.

09:26.100 --> 09:28.058
Just say it. Just say it.

09:28.100 --> 09:31.058
(WHISPERING) Fine. I
slept with my brother.

09:31.100 --> 09:33.058
What do you want from me?

09:33.100 --> 09:36.393
I want your gracious
help in finding Caleb.

09:36.435 --> 09:38.058
You know where he is.

09:38.100 --> 09:40.058
But I don't know where he is.

09:40.100 --> 09:41.058
Norma.

09:41.100 --> 09:43.058
Come on.

09:43.100 --> 09:45.058
Why are you trying to protect him,

09:45.100 --> 09:47.100
some... somebody who hurt you?

09:49.100 --> 09:51.058
Do you think that it was your fault?

09:51.100 --> 09:53.058
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

09:53.100 --> 09:55.058
It wasn't your fault.

09:55.100 --> 09:59.100
How much older was he than you, Norma?

10:00.602 --> 10:02.100
How much?

10:05.100 --> 10:07.058
Four years.

10:07.100 --> 10:10.058
He's not a nice person, Norma.

10:10.100 --> 10:11.560
He abandoned your son

10:11.602 --> 10:13.058
after he beat the shit out of me.

10:13.100 --> 10:15.810
How did he know that I
wouldn't come after Dylan?

10:20.100 --> 10:22.058
I don't know.

10:22.100 --> 10:23.560
You know, I don't know.

10:23.602 --> 10:26.393
What would it be like if
that information got out

10:26.435 --> 10:30.393
that you had a child with your brother?

10:30.435 --> 10:33.058
Your husband would find out
who he really married.

10:33.100 --> 10:35.058
Your husband's a public official.

10:35.100 --> 10:37.058
Please don't do that.

10:37.100 --> 10:41.058
Then don't put me in
this position, Norma.

10:41.100 --> 10:43.058
You do the right thing.

10:50.100 --> 10:54.100
So do you, uh... Do you like it here?

10:56.393 --> 10:58.642
"Like's" a strong word,

10:59.648 --> 11:01.606
but I do think

11:01.649 --> 11:03.650
it might be doing me some good here.

11:05.887 --> 11:07.678
That's good.

11:07.720 --> 11:09.330
Glad to hear that, Norman.

11:11.010 --> 11:12.968
Oh, have you, uh...

11:13.010 --> 11:15.662
Have you heard any
news from Emma lately?

11:18.010 --> 11:19.541
Uh, yeah.

11:19.819 --> 11:21.522
Yeah, I have.

11:21.622 --> 11:23.549
She's... you know, she's
getting better every day.

11:25.010 --> 11:26.968
Um...

11:27.010 --> 11:28.303
you know, she's getting stronger,

11:28.345 --> 11:31.968
no more tubes, so...

11:32.010 --> 11:33.968
She's, uh...

11:34.010 --> 11:36.010
She's pretty amazing.

11:42.227 --> 11:44.227
Look, Norman, there's something
that I need to tell you.

11:45.227 --> 11:47.185
You and Emma.

11:47.227 --> 11:49.227
Something happened.

11:54.937 --> 11:56.227
Yeah.

12:02.227 --> 12:04.227
Dylan, I'm... I'm glad.

12:05.227 --> 12:06.360
You are?

12:08.227 --> 12:09.185
Yeah.

12:09.227 --> 12:11.185
Yeah, I-I get it,

12:11.227 --> 12:12.185
the... the two of you.

12:12.227 --> 12:14.227
I-I really do.

12:16.227 --> 12:20.723
Oh, uh, do you remember
much about our dad?

12:23.227 --> 12:25.937
I mean, uh, your stepdad, Sam?

12:27.227 --> 12:28.185
Uh...

12:28.227 --> 12:32.185
<i>(SOMBER MUSIC)</i>

12:32.227 --> 12:34.227
You know, he, uh...

12:37.227 --> 12:39.185
He was a really unhappy man.

12:42.227 --> 12:45.185
That's probably the one
thing I remember the most.

12:45.670 --> 12:47.783
He could get really angry.

12:49.414 --> 12:51.228
And he was drunk a lot.

12:52.729 --> 12:54.595
He wasn't nice to Norma

12:56.227 --> 12:58.185
or me or... or you.

12:59.101 --> 13:00.628
You know, I don't really remember

13:00.670 --> 13:01.707
that much more, you know.

13:01.749 --> 13:04.860
I kind of, like, made a career

13:04.902 --> 13:06.895
out of not being home.

13:12.227 --> 13:14.284
Never mind. It's, uh...

13:15.505 --> 13:17.185
Don't think about it anymore.

13:17.227 --> 13:19.185
Things are good now.

13:19.227 --> 13:22.063
You're happy, and I'm getting better.

13:23.227 --> 13:24.227
Your shot.

13:26.227 --> 13:28.562
(EXHALES FORCEFULLY)

13:35.227 --> 13:36.353
We, um...

13:36.523 --> 13:38.313
I actually... I actually
hung out with him

13:38.355 --> 13:40.313
quite a bit, you know?

13:40.355 --> 13:42.022
He... he's doing really well there.

13:42.064 --> 13:44.189
Really? You really think so?

13:44.231 --> 13:45.371
Why?

13:46.354 --> 13:47.312
Uh, I... I don't know.

13:47.354 --> 13:48.277
He just...

13:49.354 --> 13:52.814
He seems like he's calmer and...

13:52.856 --> 13:55.312
I don't know... More...
he's... he's more open.

13:55.354 --> 13:56.530
Mm.

13:57.678 --> 13:59.312
I think he's just more
at peace in a way...

13:59.354 --> 14:02.114
That is the best news that
I could ever hear, Dylan.

14:07.354 --> 14:09.312
How's, uh...

14:09.354 --> 14:11.354
- Hmm?
- How's the husband?

14:13.689 --> 14:16.312
He is very good.

14:16.354 --> 14:18.312
(GIGGLES)

14:18.745 --> 14:21.312
You didn't tell Norman,
did you? He doesn't know.

14:21.354 --> 14:23.435
No, I didn't say anything to Norman.

14:25.354 --> 14:27.312
Although I don't really
understand why we all feel like

14:27.354 --> 14:29.814
it might bother him to hear that
you're seeing someone, but...

14:29.856 --> 14:31.313
Well, because it's
just... You know, he...

14:31.355 --> 14:34.189
We... we're very close,
and he's fragile.

14:34.231 --> 14:35.212
Hmm.

14:36.435 --> 14:38.312
Did it ever occur to you that
if you keep treating people

14:38.354 --> 14:39.312
like they're fragile, it might keep them

14:39.354 --> 14:41.354
from ever getting stronger?

14:44.354 --> 14:46.814
You become a philosopher in Portland?

14:46.856 --> 14:48.312
No, but I...

14:48.354 --> 14:50.312
Look, I just... I spent a lot of time

14:50.354 --> 14:52.647
thinking in the hospital, and...

14:52.689 --> 14:55.312
I'm just... I'm really impressed

14:55.354 --> 14:56.647
by how Emma just dives into
things, you know, and...

14:56.689 --> 14:58.312
Yeah. Yeah, sure.

14:58.354 --> 15:00.354
Glad Emma's got it down.

15:04.272 --> 15:06.312
<i>(GENTLE PIANO MUSIC)</i>

15:06.354 --> 15:08.642
(SIGHS) (CLEARS THROAT)

15:09.354 --> 15:10.828
I'm, uh...

15:12.354 --> 15:13.312
I'm gonna be moving to Seattle

15:13.354 --> 15:14.355
with her and her dad.

15:16.932 --> 15:18.312
There's a really great
hospital there for Emma,

15:18.354 --> 15:20.312
and she needs to be monitored a lot

15:20.354 --> 15:21.819
in the first year.

15:23.045 --> 15:24.333
I see.

15:25.533 --> 15:26.477
When?

15:27.354 --> 15:28.312
Soon.

15:28.768 --> 15:29.970
They, uh...

15:30.777 --> 15:32.312
They're renting their
house out right now,

15:32.354 --> 15:33.943
but it's on the market.

15:34.354 --> 15:35.313
And Will got a job at
a college up there.

15:35.355 --> 15:39.057
Soon like... Like, in a month?

15:40.354 --> 15:42.355
I don't know, a few days?

15:46.354 --> 15:49.624
Norma, it's gonna... It's gonna be fine.

15:51.200 --> 15:53.312
I promise, okay? It's...

15:53.354 --> 15:55.647
I'm not gonna disappear.

16:01.354 --> 16:02.354
Okay.

16:03.625 --> 16:05.312
You should come to dinner some night

16:05.354 --> 16:06.901
before you leave, okay?

16:07.354 --> 16:10.312
- Okay. I'll call you, all right?
- Okay.

16:10.354 --> 16:14.038
Dylan, I meant to ask you, have
you spoken to your dad recently?

16:16.354 --> 16:17.569
No, why?

16:19.840 --> 16:21.312
I just thought I should probably

16:21.354 --> 16:23.309
check in with him, see how he is.

16:23.690 --> 16:26.873
- Why?
- I don't know.

16:26.915 --> 16:28.722
Because he left in a hurry, and I...

16:28.765 --> 16:30.058
Don't you wonder where he is?

16:30.100 --> 16:33.058
(SIGHS) No.

16:33.100 --> 16:34.765
No, he chose to leave.

16:36.765 --> 16:38.765
Yeah, that's true.

16:41.765 --> 16:43.225
What was the name of that place

16:43.267 --> 16:44.723
where he worked in Costa Rica?

16:44.765 --> 16:46.723
It was a hotel, right?

16:46.765 --> 16:48.058
Yeah.

16:48.100 --> 16:49.765
Did it have a name?

16:53.100 --> 16:54.817
I don't remember, The...

16:55.765 --> 16:57.765
The Eden something.

16:59.064 --> 17:00.891
Norma, just leave...

17:00.933 --> 17:02.907
Leave him alone, okay?

17:03.765 --> 17:04.723
Things are good, all right?

17:04.765 --> 17:06.815
Alex is good. Norman's getting better.

17:07.765 --> 17:09.765
You don't need to check up on Caleb.

17:12.099 --> 17:14.224
This is... this is coming

17:14.267 --> 17:15.723
from some sort of wrong
place, all right?

17:15.765 --> 17:18.723
Just don't... Don't do
something destructive.

17:19.368 --> 17:20.766
I won't.

17:23.765 --> 17:24.723
(SIGHS)

17:24.765 --> 17:26.239
All right, I'll, um,

17:27.765 --> 17:28.723
see you later.

17:28.765 --> 17:29.723
I gotta pack up some more stuff,

17:29.765 --> 17:30.723
so I'll be back late tonight.

17:31.392 --> 17:33.723
Okay, all right. Bye, Dylan.

17:40.471 --> 17:41.429
<i>(TOUCH TONES BEEPING)</i>

17:41.471 --> 17:43.429
<i>(LINE TRILLS)</i>

17:43.797 --> 17:44.755
<i>Hola, buenas noches.</i>

17:44.797 --> 17:46.755
<i>Lago Eden. ¿Cómo puedo ayudarle?</i>

17:46.797 --> 17:47.755
Um, hello, does someone

17:47.797 --> 17:50.755
named Caleb Calhoun still work there?

17:50.797 --> 17:52.797
<i>One moment, please.</i>

17:54.797 --> 17:56.797
(SIGHS)

17:57.797 --> 17:58.965
<i>Hello?</i>

18:02.797 --> 18:03.756
<i>Hello?</i>

18:04.439 --> 18:05.796
<i>Who's this?</i>

18:08.674 --> 18:10.465
It's, um...

18:10.507 --> 18:12.016
It's Norma Louise.

18:13.057 --> 18:14.755
(LATIN MUSIC PLAYING)

18:15.370 --> 18:16.454
Norma.

18:17.797 --> 18:19.797
Oh, it's so good to hear your voice.

18:23.797 --> 18:25.299
<i>Is... is everything okay?</i>

18:27.797 --> 18:28.910
Is Dylan okay?

18:29.708 --> 18:32.465
We... we just never heard

18:32.507 --> 18:33.755
from you after you left,

18:33.797 --> 18:37.755
so I just wanted to make
sure that you're okay.

18:37.797 --> 18:39.090
I'm sorry.

18:39.132 --> 18:40.755
Um...

18:40.797 --> 18:42.755
look, I got myself into a bad situation

18:42.797 --> 18:45.755
before I left, and I was just worried

18:45.797 --> 18:48.027
about what the fallout was gonna be.

18:48.070 --> 18:49.616
And if there was a fallout,

18:49.716 --> 18:51.716
I just didn't want it to be on you guys.

18:53.593 --> 18:55.051
I see.

18:58.716 --> 19:00.716
Hey, how's Dylan?

19:05.051 --> 19:06.674
He's... He's doing great.

19:06.716 --> 19:10.674
He has a... a girlfriend that
he's pretty serious about.

19:10.716 --> 19:13.674
Is it Emma?

19:13.716 --> 19:14.674
<i>Yeah.</i>

19:14.716 --> 19:16.674
Did she have the surgery?

19:17.460 --> 19:19.674
Yeah. Uh, yeah, she did.

19:19.716 --> 19:21.384
She... she's doing very well.

19:21.631 --> 19:22.589
<i>(CHUCKLES)</i>

19:22.631 --> 19:23.879
I'm glad.

19:23.921 --> 19:25.879
That's so good to hear, Norma.

19:25.921 --> 19:29.878
<i>Thank you for telling me that.</i>

19:30.678 --> 19:32.117
And... and I m...

19:32.866 --> 19:34.253
I miss you both.

19:35.892 --> 19:37.057
Mm-hmm.

19:38.225 --> 19:39.878
<i>You know, I think of you</i>

19:39.920 --> 19:42.542
<i>all the time, every day.</i>

19:42.920 --> 19:44.227
<i>And Dylan,</i>

19:45.243 --> 19:46.727
every day.

19:47.630 --> 19:49.878
<i>You know, you... you should call Dylan.</i>

19:50.765 --> 19:52.879
Because I... I think he's...

19:52.921 --> 19:55.385
He's very hurt that you left.

19:58.920 --> 20:02.920
I know, and I'm sorry.

20:05.920 --> 20:06.878
(SIGHS)

20:06.920 --> 20:08.920
I have to go.

20:10.630 --> 20:11.878
Okay.

20:11.920 --> 20:13.878
I love you.

20:13.920 --> 20:16.878
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

20:21.920 --> 20:23.878
Good-bye, Caleb.

20:34.920 --> 20:36.630
I'm in my bed.

20:38.356 --> 20:39.314
It's the middle of the night,

20:39.357 --> 20:41.921
and I have my stuffed bear with me.

20:42.920 --> 20:45.878
I remember him.

20:45.920 --> 20:47.878
I haven't thought about him in a while.

20:47.920 --> 20:48.878
I always slept with him

20:48.920 --> 20:50.920
when I wasn't in my mother's bed.

20:52.920 --> 20:54.256
How old are you?

20:55.457 --> 20:56.604
Seven.

20:58.088 --> 21:00.920
Why aren't you in your
mom's bed tonight?

21:04.630 --> 21:06.920
Mother told me Dad had been drinking...

21:08.920 --> 21:11.878
That I should go to my room

21:11.920 --> 21:13.878
and get in bed and be very quiet.

21:13.920 --> 21:15.878
And so I did.

21:15.920 --> 21:16.878
(THUNDER BOOMING)

21:16.920 --> 21:17.824
<i>But I woke up.</i>

21:19.920 --> 21:21.891
<i>And I'm thirsty.</i>

21:23.920 --> 21:25.268
<i>I walk</i>

21:25.920 --> 21:27.968
<i>very quietly down the hall,</i>

21:29.906 --> 21:32.862
<i>afraid to go to the kitchen
to get a glass of water</i>

21:32.962 --> 21:34.878
<i>because I know my dad
might still be awake.</i>

21:34.920 --> 21:37.878
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

21:41.920 --> 21:44.588
(WATER DRIPPING)

22:14.422 --> 22:15.879
(DISH RATTLES)

22:30.920 --> 22:32.829
I'm sorry, Norman.

22:33.797 --> 22:35.870
You know I love you, don't you?

22:36.303 --> 22:37.303
I know, Daddy.

22:37.346 --> 22:38.304
I know, Daddy.

22:44.346 --> 22:45.659
It's okay, Norman.

22:46.593 --> 22:48.389
Remember, you're just watching.

22:49.303 --> 22:51.671
You can get up and leave
anytime you like.

22:57.346 --> 22:58.621
I'm right here, Norman.

23:06.245 --> 23:09.245
(RAIN PATTERING)

23:12.311 --> 23:14.267
I thought you didn't
want to be seen with me.

23:14.309 --> 23:15.578
I don't.

23:19.857 --> 23:20.857
Pick it up.

23:24.857 --> 23:27.815
<i>(TENSE MUSIC)</i>

23:42.857 --> 23:44.377
How much money do you want?

23:44.420 --> 23:47.087
I don't... I don't want any.

23:57.129 --> 24:00.129
(CELL PHONE CHIMING)

24:07.065 --> 24:08.023
Hello?

24:08.419 --> 24:09.377
Hey, Dylan.

24:09.419 --> 24:10.550
It's your dad.

24:11.419 --> 24:13.377
<i>(LATIN MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

24:13.419 --> 24:14.377
Hey.

24:14.419 --> 24:15.730
<i>Hey, how are you?</i>

24:18.587 --> 24:19.874
Did Norma call you?

24:21.100 --> 24:22.377
<i>Yeah, yeah.</i>

24:22.784 --> 24:25.377
Dylan, I left because I thought

24:25.419 --> 24:27.413
it was the right thing
to do for everyone.

24:28.650 --> 24:29.457
<i>Okay.</i>

24:29.595 --> 24:31.501
I mean, it wasn't what I wanted to do.

24:33.419 --> 24:36.419
There's not a day that goes
by I don't think of you.

24:41.218 --> 24:44.218
Look, I miss you.

24:47.860 --> 24:49.207
I miss you too.

24:49.860 --> 24:50.818
<i>And I'm gonna come up and see you</i>

24:50.860 --> 24:52.528
<i>as... as soon as I think, um,</i>

24:52.570 --> 24:53.818
it's safe.

24:53.860 --> 24:56.860
You know, maybe move up there for good.

24:59.195 --> 25:02.153
<i>(GENTLE MUSIC)</i>

25:02.195 --> 25:03.860
Yeah, that'd be good.

25:05.860 --> 25:07.818
<i>That'd be good.</i>

25:07.860 --> 25:09.861
Hey, I, uh...

25:10.860 --> 25:11.818
I gotta go.

25:11.860 --> 25:12.861
But, um...

25:14.860 --> 25:15.818
<i>It's good to hear from you.</i>

25:15.860 --> 25:17.818
Yeah, you too, Dylan.

25:17.860 --> 25:19.818
<i>Take care, Dad.</i>

25:19.860 --> 25:21.037
<i>Bye.</i>

25:21.737 --> 25:23.028
All right, bye.

25:37.570 --> 25:39.860
(RAIN PATTERING)

25:43.860 --> 25:46.818
<i>(EERIE MUSIC)</i>

26:24.860 --> 26:26.860
You have something for me?

26:41.860 --> 26:43.818
(GUN COCKS)

26:43.860 --> 26:46.818
<i>(TENSE MUSIC)</i>

27:01.860 --> 27:03.861
(GASPING)

27:08.860 --> 27:11.860
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

27:13.861 --> 27:16.818
I can't get Caleb killed,

27:17.585 --> 27:19.346
and I can't kill you,

27:19.695 --> 27:21.392
so I'm screwed.

27:22.023 --> 27:23.818
I'm screwed!

27:24.293 --> 27:25.251
You got me!

27:26.241 --> 27:29.211
All I wanted was my
freaking window fixed,

27:29.254 --> 27:31.607
and now you're gonna destroy my life!

27:32.285 --> 27:34.211
So just go right ahead.

27:34.254 --> 27:37.336
Just go right the hell ahead!

27:38.254 --> 27:41.212
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

28:03.759 --> 28:06.759
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

28:09.571 --> 28:13.529
(KNIFE CHOPPING HEAVILY)

28:13.571 --> 28:14.648
Hey.

28:15.906 --> 28:16.809
Hey.

28:17.571 --> 28:18.471
You okay?

28:19.981 --> 28:20.939
Yeah, I'm great.

28:21.479 --> 28:22.229
Okay.

28:22.271 --> 28:23.939
I just, um...

28:23.981 --> 28:25.229
I just came to get some of my stuff.

28:25.778 --> 28:27.409
Okay, have fun leaving me.

28:28.271 --> 28:30.229
(CHOPPING RESUMES)

28:30.271 --> 28:31.627
Norma...

28:32.271 --> 28:33.229
- Norma.
- I'm fine, okay?

28:33.271 --> 28:34.939
I'm just in a bad mood.

28:35.836 --> 28:37.271
I don't want to talk about it.

28:40.271 --> 28:42.229
Okay.

28:42.271 --> 28:43.564
I'll see you later.

28:43.606 --> 28:45.271
Yep.

29:28.981 --> 29:31.939
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

30:35.557 --> 30:38.557
I'd like you to talk some
more about your father.

30:40.557 --> 30:42.557
What do you want to know?

30:44.168 --> 30:45.515
He was an alcoholic?

30:45.935 --> 30:47.514
Not officially.

30:47.557 --> 30:49.557
He didn't think he was.

30:50.342 --> 30:52.300
But he drank a lot?

30:52.728 --> 30:54.728
Don't talk about it, Norman.

30:57.267 --> 30:58.515
Why are you here?

30:58.557 --> 30:59.850
I don't want you thinking about this

30:59.892 --> 31:01.515
or talking about it.

31:01.557 --> 31:03.515
I have to, Mother. And
you can't be here.

31:03.557 --> 31:05.557
I have to be here. You're
not listening to me.

31:07.557 --> 31:09.557
Is she here, Norman?

31:11.558 --> 31:13.934
She doesn't want me to talk to you.

31:16.557 --> 31:17.850
Can I talk to her?

31:32.948 --> 31:34.557
I'm right here.

31:36.557 --> 31:38.515
Just leave him alone.

31:38.557 --> 31:40.850
If you want to ask him
something, ask me.

31:42.254 --> 31:44.515
Why don't you want him
to talk for himself?

31:44.557 --> 31:46.515
Because there's things
that have happened,

31:47.259 --> 31:48.915
things that he does
not need to remember.

31:48.958 --> 31:50.916
And I have worked very hard

31:50.958 --> 31:51.916
to make him forget about these things,

31:51.958 --> 31:53.926
and I don't need you undoing it.

31:55.690 --> 31:57.916
I think it might help him.

31:57.958 --> 31:59.917
I was there. It won't help him.

31:59.959 --> 32:01.612
It will crush him.

32:03.689 --> 32:05.192
Don't blame me.

32:06.449 --> 32:07.898
It's not my fault.

32:09.044 --> 32:11.084
I didn't realize who I had married,

32:11.126 --> 32:13.959
how ill he was, and I
didn't know how to leave.

32:16.898 --> 32:18.185
I tried once.

32:20.264 --> 32:21.571
I got Norman,

32:22.496 --> 32:23.916
and I packed a bag,

32:23.958 --> 32:25.645
and we got in the car and left.

32:25.688 --> 32:27.916
But I couldn't leave because
I couldn't find Dylan.

32:27.958 --> 32:28.917
He wasn't home.

32:28.959 --> 32:30.916
And we were just driving
around the neighborhood

32:30.958 --> 32:31.847
trying to find him.

32:32.958 --> 32:34.084
<i>Sam found us,</i>

32:34.126 --> 32:36.793
<i>got in the car, held a gun to my head,</i>

32:36.835 --> 32:38.916
<i>and made me drive back to the house.</i>

32:38.958 --> 32:41.064
What the hell did you
think you were doing?

32:41.958 --> 32:42.917
Do you think you can just...

32:42.959 --> 32:44.586
(SHOUTING) Walk out on me?

32:44.959 --> 32:46.958
Just leave me here?

32:48.958 --> 32:50.793
Sam! No!

32:50.835 --> 32:51.916
I'll kill us all, Norma!

32:51.958 --> 32:53.626
- (SHRIEKS)
- Daddy.

32:53.668 --> 32:56.418
Sorry! I'm sorry. I ju...

32:56.460 --> 32:57.916
You're right. You're right, Sam.

32:57.958 --> 32:59.916
Just... let's just go inside. (SMOOCHES)

32:59.958 --> 33:00.917
Okay? I-I could never leave you.

33:00.959 --> 33:03.916
You know that. All right? (SMOOCHES)

33:03.958 --> 33:05.916
(WHISPERING) Honey, go inside the house.

33:05.958 --> 33:07.126
Hide. Hide.

33:08.958 --> 33:09.916
I-I just... I was mad.

33:09.958 --> 33:11.293
Okay, baby?

33:12.958 --> 33:14.668
(CLOTHING UNZIPS)

33:16.668 --> 33:18.916
(SIGHS)

33:18.958 --> 33:19.916
Okay.

33:19.958 --> 33:21.264
Sam.

33:22.958 --> 33:25.916
<i>(DARK OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

33:27.958 --> 33:29.126
(CLOTHING TEARS)

33:30.958 --> 33:31.958
(SPITS)

33:33.835 --> 33:36.958
(GRUNTING)

33:42.126 --> 33:45.293
(PANTING AND GROANING)

33:46.958 --> 33:49.916
<i>(DRAMATIC PIANO MUSIC)</i>

34:00.459 --> 34:03.127
I don't want him to know these things.

34:03.169 --> 34:05.459
It will kill both of us.

34:09.458 --> 34:12.417
Please, Doctor, if you have a heart,

34:12.458 --> 34:14.417
don't make him remember these things.

34:14.458 --> 34:17.417
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

34:26.081 --> 34:28.871
Or I will have to do something about it.

34:40.983 --> 34:42.592
- Oh, hey.
- Hi.

34:43.274 --> 34:46.106
Sit down. Everything's ready.

34:47.449 --> 34:49.206
- You okay?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

34:49.248 --> 34:51.206
- Sit down.
- Oh, you know what?

34:51.248 --> 34:52.708
Chick's here with the window.
I'm just gonna help him.

34:52.750 --> 34:53.757
Chick?

34:53.911 --> 34:54.869
Yeah, he's just got the window...

34:54.911 --> 34:56.130
What did he say to you?

34:57.427 --> 34:58.746
He said, "I got the window.

34:58.788 --> 35:00.869
I could use some help unloading it."

35:01.621 --> 35:03.621
- Oh.
- What's wrong?

35:06.911 --> 35:09.869
<i>(GENTLE PIANO MUSIC)</i>

35:09.911 --> 35:11.607
I just, um...

35:14.509 --> 35:16.027
I love you.

35:17.033 --> 35:18.788
I want you to know that.

35:22.911 --> 35:24.869
You're telling me this right now?

35:25.177 --> 35:26.301
Yeah.

35:29.911 --> 35:32.037
Well, I love you too.

35:36.911 --> 35:40.119
- I'll be right back, you know.
- Okay.

35:53.413 --> 35:54.869
(SIGHS)

35:54.911 --> 35:58.037
All right. (GRUNTS)

35:58.079 --> 36:00.746
Okay, easy. Almost there.

36:00.788 --> 36:02.869
Is there somewhere we can set it down?

36:02.911 --> 36:05.911
Yeah, you can set it down right here.

36:08.788 --> 36:09.869
Hello, Norma.

36:09.911 --> 36:12.869
Yeah, hello.

36:12.911 --> 36:13.869
- There we go.
- Easy.

36:13.911 --> 36:15.869
That's good.

36:15.911 --> 36:19.037
I'd... I'd like to unwrap it
so that I could show you.

36:19.079 --> 36:21.037
(SCOFFS)

36:21.079 --> 36:23.743
(MIRTHLESS CHUCKLE)

36:24.816 --> 36:26.675
Yeah, no... Yeah, we'd love to see it.

36:30.912 --> 36:32.869
That's great.

36:32.911 --> 36:34.204
That's really... That's amazing.

36:34.246 --> 36:35.869
That's really beautiful, Chick.

36:36.737 --> 36:38.102
You know what they say,

36:38.584 --> 36:40.542
you never know what you're capable of

36:40.585 --> 36:42.585
until you're tested.

36:45.295 --> 36:46.543
Isn't that right?

36:46.585 --> 36:47.543
Gee, what are you saying?

36:47.585 --> 36:50.543
Are you saying that we all have things

36:50.585 --> 36:52.347
"hidden" inside us?

36:53.369 --> 36:55.204
Secrets we don't want anyone to know,

36:55.246 --> 36:56.327
things that other people might know

36:56.369 --> 36:58.327
and hold over your head,
even though you personally

36:58.369 --> 37:00.683
have done nothing to them?

37:01.590 --> 37:03.327
I think he was just talking
about the window, Norma.

37:03.369 --> 37:05.327
You're gonna be packing your bags soon,

37:05.369 --> 37:06.659
so just... Just stay out of it.

37:09.081 --> 37:10.721
Go ahead, tough guy.

37:11.028 --> 37:13.326
Come on, do what you're gonna do.

37:13.369 --> 37:15.204
Okay, break the woman in half.

37:15.246 --> 37:17.327
But you know what? I'm not broken.

37:17.369 --> 37:19.327
I am still standing.

37:19.369 --> 37:20.327
So go ahead.

37:20.369 --> 37:24.928
Do your best, you giant, lame asshole!

37:25.369 --> 37:28.327
<i>(OMINOUS MUSIC)</i>

37:35.369 --> 37:37.302
I hope

37:39.246 --> 37:41.327
you enjoy your new window,

37:41.369 --> 37:43.369
Norma Bates.

37:45.369 --> 37:46.369
(SMOOCHES)

37:56.369 --> 37:58.369
You can mail me a check.

38:03.369 --> 38:05.327
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

38:17.055 --> 38:19.055
What the hell?

38:21.369 --> 38:23.369
What the hell? What was that?

38:32.369 --> 38:33.238
What?

38:40.771 --> 38:42.328
When I was, um,

38:42.967 --> 38:46.369
a teenager... It was a
long time ago... um...

38:48.989 --> 38:51.079
I slept with my brother.

38:54.345 --> 38:55.326
I'm sorry.

38:55.369 --> 38:57.772
God, I'm sorry to have to tell you this.

38:59.612 --> 39:01.327
Oh, it's horrible.

39:01.369 --> 39:02.751
I'm sorry.

39:03.607 --> 39:05.230
He's Dylan's father.

39:08.369 --> 39:10.327
The guy that I had dinner with?

39:10.369 --> 39:12.369
Caleb, yeah.

39:18.136 --> 39:19.984
Norma, you... you were young.

39:20.106 --> 39:21.327
It... it was a mistake.

39:21.369 --> 39:24.110
Mistake? It was not a mistake.

39:24.153 --> 39:25.143
It was a way of life.

39:26.582 --> 39:28.327
It happened for years.

39:28.704 --> 39:29.789
I loved him.

39:31.066 --> 39:33.024
Our home life was torture,

39:33.067 --> 39:34.899
and we were all we had.

39:39.632 --> 39:42.422
I finally tried to stop it, and, um,

39:43.445 --> 39:44.857
he got really upset

39:44.899 --> 39:46.021
and he raped me.

39:54.545 --> 39:56.503
You know how horrible it is to be raped

39:56.546 --> 39:57.672
by someone you love?

39:57.879 --> 39:58.879
(SNIFFLES)

40:01.135 --> 40:02.425
And I hate him.

40:04.299 --> 40:06.239
I hate him. I hate him.

40:06.282 --> 40:08.240
But I don't hate him enough

40:08.282 --> 40:09.420
to hurt him.

40:11.456 --> 40:14.072
And it's a mess because I don't know

40:14.114 --> 40:17.970
if part of why I hate Caleb so much

40:18.903 --> 40:21.112
is because I hate myself.

40:25.114 --> 40:26.282
(SNIFFLES)

40:29.876 --> 40:31.957
All in a day's work.

40:32.633 --> 40:35.591
<i>(DRAMATIC MUSIC)</i>

40:35.838 --> 40:37.796
So now you know who you're married to.

40:37.838 --> 40:39.796
And I should have told you before,

40:39.838 --> 40:42.617
but I've never loved anyone enough

40:43.340 --> 40:44.796
to feel obligated

40:44.838 --> 40:46.224
to be honest with them.

40:48.838 --> 40:49.650
And...

40:55.715 --> 40:56.506
And I just...

40:56.548 --> 40:58.156
It... it sucks.

40:58.380 --> 41:01.257
It sucks because I can't hide.

41:03.379 --> 41:04.337
And I want to, but I can't.

41:04.379 --> 41:06.006
And Chick found out.

41:06.379 --> 41:08.337
He met Caleb when he was up at the farm

41:08.379 --> 41:09.337
working with Dylan.

41:09.379 --> 41:11.574
He... he just figured it out.

41:13.379 --> 41:14.986
And he has issues with my brother,

41:15.029 --> 41:18.264
and he was trying to
find him, and he told me

41:18.560 --> 41:21.518
that if I didn't help him

41:21.560 --> 41:24.032
that he would tell you all of this,

41:25.038 --> 41:27.519
that he would spread it around town,

41:27.945 --> 41:30.969
and that he would humiliate you.

41:33.560 --> 41:34.799
So...

41:35.560 --> 41:36.728
So...

41:38.561 --> 41:40.560
I don't know.

41:43.859 --> 41:45.859
Just go pack your bag.

41:54.186 --> 41:56.186
Okay.

42:01.560 --> 42:03.213
Where we going?

42:09.728 --> 42:13.686
(SOBBING)

